       <shortlink>api desktop api object class active drilldown function</shortlink>
   <topic>OBJECT.ACTIVE_DRILLDOWN Function</topic>
   <description>Returns the name of the deepest control that has focus.</description>
   <syntax>Object_Name as C = .Active_Drilldown([L force_active_children])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>force_active_children</name>
         <description>Optional. For internal use only.
</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <discussion><![CDATA[
The <OBJECT>.ACTIVE_DRILLDOWN() method applies to:]]>
   </discussion>
   
   <sections>
   
    <section>
            <list>
            <item>
            <name><![CDATA[Alpha Anywhere (for <OBJECT> use the keyword "A5")]]></name>
            </item>
            
             <item>
            <name><![CDATA[Browses (for <OBJECT> use either the <BROWSE> pointer or the name of the browse)]]></name>
            </item>
            
             <item>
            <name><![CDATA[Forms (for <OBJECT> use either the <FORM> pointer or the name of the form)]]></name>
            </item>
            
            
            
            </list>
            
            
            
       </section>
   
       <section>
            <description><![CDATA[The <OBJECT>.ACTIVE_DRILLDOWN() method returns the address of the deepest control that has focus.]]>
</description>
           
       </section>
   </sections>
   
     <sections>
       <section>
            
            <example><![CDATA[active_field = topparent.Active_Drilldown()
dim ptr as P
ptr = browse.view("CustomerBrowse")
? ptr.Active_Drilldown() ? ":CustomerBrowse:First_Name"]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
   <limitations>Desktop applications only.</limitations>
   
